// SMACH Transpiler
// Converts YAML state machine definitions (SMACH format) into Mermaid flowchart TD syntax.

State types are mapped to Mermaid node shapes: container types become subgraphs,
action states become stadium shapes, monitor/service states become hexagons, etc.

FUNCTION toNodeId(name, prefix) -> string
  Sanitize name by replacing non-alphanumeric characters with underscores.
  IF prefix provided, prepend it with an underscore separator.

---

FUNCTION nodeDeclaration(id, label, type) -> string
  Look up the shape for the state type. Return the Mermaid node syntax for that shape
  (stadium, hexagon, diamond, parallelogram, trapezoid, or rounded rectangle).

---

FUNCTION processStates(states, lines, externalLinks, prefix, initialState, indent, parentOutcomes, parentOutcomePrefix) -> void
  Recursively process a states map to produce Mermaid lines.
  For each state:
    IF the state type maps to 'subgraph' (container):
      Open a subgraph block. Add an internal start node pointing to the initial_state if present.
      Recursively call processStates for child states, passing this container's outcomes.
      Add outcome nodes inside the subgraph, then close it.
      Add external links from outcome nodes to their transition targets (sibling states or parent outcomes).
    ELSE (leaf state):
      Emit a node declaration. For each transition, determine if the target is a parent outcome
      or a sibling state and emit an arrow with the outcome label.

---

FUNCTION transpile(yamlText) -> { mermaid }                                             EXPORT
  CALLS: processStates (smach-transpiler)
  Parse YAML. Throw if smach_diagram root or root StateMachine is missing or malformed.
  Start with "flowchart TD". Add a START node pointing to the root machine's initial state.
  Call processStates on the root machine's states.
  Add root-level outcome nodes. Append external container-outcome links as a labeled section.
  Return { mermaid: joined lines }.

---

FUNCTION isSmachYaml(text) -> boolean                                                   EXPORT
  Return true if the text contains a smach_diagram: root key (via regex).
